        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Fairfield Con.</placeName>
                <date>July 13. 1854</date>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>,
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir/Have the kindness to send<lb/> me the <date>July</date>
                Number of the Occident to this place, whether I have<lb/> removed with the
                    views<add>?</add> of rusticating for some time.â€” May I<lb/> also trouble you
                with the following commission, as I know no one<lb/> in your place, whom I could
                address for that purpose. Since <persName>Dr<lb/> Raphall</persName> has begun
                publishing his Postbiblical history of the Jews<lb/> in the <hi rend="underline"
                    >Philadelphia Sunday Dispatch</hi>, I have been a sub-<lb/>scriber to the paper.
                Now, my copy being sent to <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, I<lb/> am interrupted
                in the perusal of the Drs history, and would, therefore<lb/> most respectfully beg
                you, to buy the numbers of <del><date>July</date></del>
                <date>June 18</date>, <date>June 25</date>,<lb/>
                <date>July 2</date>, <date>July 9</date> &amp; <date>July 16</date> and send them to
                me with the Occident.<lb/> My <date>August</date> number of the Occident you will be
                kind enough<lb/> to send me, directed to the care of <persName>Mrs S.
                    Mayer</persName>, <placeName>412 Grand<lb/> Str. N. York</placeName>, whither,
                if you will oblige me still more, you<lb/> might send me also <del>from</del> the
                continuations of the Sunday Dis-<lb/>patch from <date>July 23</date> to <date>Aug
                    20</date>., the time of my absence from <placeName>Ch.</placeName><lb/> In
                passing through <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, I shall take pleasure in
                re-<lb/>funding you all outlays.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Ever ready to serve you in return,</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Your, most friendly</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Dr M Mayer</persName>
            </p>
            <p>care of <persName>Mr John A Philips</persName>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Fairfield, Con.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
